Introduction

I am a very self-oriented person and I took the instruction of this project being useful very personally. So I chose the data source as self-oriented as possible which was my diary(more like a autobiography of my life so far) from last year. I spent about 6 monthes writing 5 chapters in total, and here I picked the first two of them. The translation was conducted via Google translator, so some of the context might be lost.

  • First data processing

Since the main purpose of my diary was about looking back into my first thirty years and organizing my inner navigating principles, I classified every chapter with a specific theme. I was curious of my word usage in the diary, wondering whether the frequently used words would fit the theme properly as it is meant to be. So I used the basic bar graph to display the top 10 used words nicely.

First chapter was titled as memory of discrepancy, but the translator only processed discrepancy as gap. Nevertheless, it was not the most used word of the chapter, but it was time, and lovefollowing after.

Notably, some words like im, couldnt, and ha was included in the original rankings. couldnt might show a little significance for indicating the negative connotation, but ha and im is far less valuable. So I manually excluded those three words along with the stop words that was removed in advance.

  • Second chapter

I repeated the process for the second chapter.

file_path_2 <- "C:/Users/82109/Desktop/project_template/30diary_2.txt"

text_2<- readLines(file_path_2)


df_2 <- tibble(text = text_2) %>%
  unnest_tokens(word, text) %>%
  mutate(word = str_remove_all(word, "[^[:alnum:]]")) %>%
  filter(!word %in% stop_words$word) %>% 
    filter(!word %in% c("ha")) 
 


top_words_2 <- df_2 %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE) %>%
  head(10)


word_plot_2 <- ggplot(data = top_words_2, aes(x = n, y = reorder(word, n))) +
  geom_col(fill = "purple") +
  xlab("Frequency") +
  ylab("Word") +
  ggtitle("Diary_2 : 10 Most Frequently Used Words") +
  coord_flip()  #  


print(word_plot_2)

Second chapter was titled as organizing of deficiency, and the word deficiency was on the first rank. ha was the only word to exclude in the top 10 ranks.

  • What to do more?

Since this analysis is not mainly for breaking down complex static figure but for visualizing my word frequency to help organize my thoughts, none other than word cloud seems like an appropriate method to choose. However, top 10 used words are not abundant enough to visualize the chapter, so I increased the numbers to 50.

# creating word clouds
create_wordcloud_blue <- function(top_words, title) {
  wordcloud(words = top_words$word,
            freq = top_words$n,
            scale = c(5, 0.5),
            max.words = 50,
            random.order = FALSE,
            rot.per = 0.3,
            colors = brewer.pal(9, "Blues"),
            main = title)
}

create_wordcloud_purple <- function(top_words, title) {
  wordcloud(words = top_words$word,
            freq = top_words$n,
            scale = c(5, 0.5),
            max.words = 50,
            random.order = FALSE,
            rot.per = 0.3,
            colors = brewer.pal(9, "Purples"),
            main = title)
}

Also, I tried to figure out the common most frequently used word in two chapters, and make one word cloud.

# first graph frequency count
word_freq_1 <- df_1 %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE)

# second graph frequency count
word_freq_2 <- df_2 %>%
  count(word, sort = TRUE)

# extracting common words
common_words <- word_freq_1 %>%
  inner_join(word_freq_2, by = "word", suffix = c(".Ch1", ".Ch2")) %>% # trying to tidy the name
  mutate(total_freq = n.Ch1 + n.Ch2) %>%
  arrange(desc(total_freq)) %>%
  head(50)
